As she walked through the village, she noted that it was quiet, noone was really out, and the few that were, wwere all heading in the same direction. Shrugging her shoulders, she headed in the same direction behind them. <br>
<br>
Once she reached the destination, it looked like they were having some celebration, racking her brain, she remembered the date and smiled. It was a feast for Artemis, it was May. Seeing as she had met Artemis once or twice, she smiled and headed over. She caught a glimps of Melousa who showed up, and slid into a shadow, watching her.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#993300>(5/10/03 10:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To Flirt or Not to Flirt?</span><hr size=1> Theseus watched as Delerium resumed her place and began to watch from the back as she nursed her drink.  He moved to lean against the wall close to her, but not too close as he did not wish to violate her personal space and make her feel uncomfortable.  &quot;It's a good night for a festival.&quot;  He started a bit hesitant as to what to say to this warrior queen.  &quot;The drink is good, surely that is a blessing from Dionysus.&quot;  He bit his bottom lip, cringing thinking that it was not a good thing to bring up the name of another god at a celebration for the goddess.  He cleared his throat and shifted on his feet.  He wanted to make a graceful exit from the festivities prior to the sacrifice.  He did not believe that he could stand by and allow a sacrifice, no matter how service oriented, no matter to what goddess.  There were just some things that even a young warrior in training such as himself could not stomach.  &quot;Would it be acceptable for me to spend this evening in the tavern?  I do not want to cause any problems by remaining in the village.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Platinum Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 947<br> <font color=#993300>(5/11/03 7:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=54>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It was time</span><hr size=1> As Hippolyte stood enjoying the sights of the festival, one of the guards quickly walked up to her and whispered.  Hippolyte frowned and sent the guard to Elektra.  She was told that there had been trouble with Cyanna and her little brother.  And Hippolyte would not have the important ceremony threatened by a little illithios.  <br>
